<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1088,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1088,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[279,473,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[279,473,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">Myolepta pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[479,568,1088,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[479,568,1088,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Strobl" authorityName="Strobl" box="[715,949,1088,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difformis">
<emphasis box="[715,853,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. difformis</emphasis>
(Strobl)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1061,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[960,1061,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1074,1192,1089,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trojana">
<emphasis box="[1074,1192,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. trojana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer" authorityName="Panzer" box="[1246,1436,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis box="[1246,1335,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. vara</emphasis>
(Panzer)
</taxonomicName>
in the pointed inner projection of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[759,831,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
Fig. 
<number box="[816,831,1124,1149]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) (with blunt, rounded inner projection in the latter species). It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[557,688,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[557,688,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the orange colouration of the abdomen (wholly black in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Harris" authorityName="Harris" box="[428,633,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potens">
<emphasis box="[428,538,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. potens</emphasis>
(Harris)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reemer &amp; Hauser" authorityName="Reemer &amp; Hauser" box="[687,994,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mada">
<emphasis box="[687,786,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. mada</emphasis>
Reemer &amp; Hauser
</taxonomicName>
in its narrow black median facial stripe (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1232,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1436,1459]" captionTargetBox="[219,1402,252,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1412]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 1. Adult, lateral view; 2. Mesonotum, lateral view; 3. Head, lateral view; 4. Head, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255697/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,1232,1256]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). The shape of the hypandrium (nearly parallel or slightly converging laterally to apex in ventral view) and the pilosity of the mesonotum (yellowish-white erect hairs) (
<figureCitation box="[861,932,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1436,1459]" captionTargetBox="[219,1402,252,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1412]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 1. Adult, lateral view; 2. Mesonotum, lateral view; 3. Head, lateral view; 4. Head, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255697/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
Fig. 
<number box="[917,932,1269,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) are similar in 
<taxonomicName box="[1117,1239,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1117,1239,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1250,1343,1268,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1343,1268,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName box="[324,442,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii">
<emphasis box="[324,442,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the orange posterior margin of abdominal tergites 
<number box="[1118,1132,1304,1328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[1187,1201,1304,1328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="4.0">4</number>
(entirely black in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the anterolateral orange spots on tergite 
<number box="[791,807,1341,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="3.0">3</number>
, which do not reach the posterior margin of the tergite. Additional differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[513,632,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii">
<emphasis box="[513,632,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[689,845,1377,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[689,845,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are listed in 
<tableCitation box="[994,1079,1376,1401]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,1588,1611]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,1639,1990]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological differences between males of M. pazukii sp. nov. and M. nigritarsis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/09F6666F1036D216769BDC63B3886E03" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" tableUuid="09F6666F1036D216769BDC63B3886E03">
Table 
<number box="[1064,1079,1376,1400]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
. The colour pattern in legs and abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[270,337,1412,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,337,1412,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) is shared between 
<taxonomicName box="[563,682,1412,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[563,682,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[690,781,1412,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[690,781,1412,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reemer &amp; Hauser" authorityName="Reemer &amp; Hauser" box="[836,1261,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carthaginiensis">
<emphasis box="[836,1048,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. carthaginiensis</emphasis>
Reemer &amp; Hauser
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName box="[1317,1436,1412,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pazukii">
<emphasis box="[1317,1436,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. pazukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[295,506,1448,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carthaginiensis">
<emphasis box="[295,506,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. carthaginiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following characters: lateral margins of hypandrium in ventral view nearly parallel (
<figureCitation box="[252,322,1484,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">
Fig. 
<number box="[307,322,1485,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) (convex in 
<taxonomicName box="[469,681,1484,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carthaginiensis">
<emphasis box="[469,681,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="277">M. carthaginiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and anterior half of mesonotum with yellowish-white erect hairs instead of golden appressed hairs.
</paragraph>
