<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1528,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">Description. MALE.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[607,697,1529,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[715,784,1528,1553]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1436,1459]" captionTargetBox="[219,1402,252,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1412]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 1. Adult, lateral view; 2. Mesonotum, lateral view; 3. Head, lateral view; 4. Head, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255697/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[771,784,1529,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[811,874,1528,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[893,1000,1528,1553]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1436,1459]" captionTargetBox="[219,1402,252,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1412]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 1. Adult, lateral view; 2. Mesonotum, lateral view; 3. Head, lateral view; 4. Head, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255697/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">
Figs 
<number box="[954,1000,1529,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eye contiguity about 
<number box="[1273,1283,1529,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1293,1309,1529,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="2.0">2</number>
as long as ocellar triangle; face at level of median facial tubercle about 
<number box="[826,861,1565,1589]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="0.4">0.4</number>
times as wide as total width of head; facial tubercle rounded; face black, predominantly pruinose, except for a median narrow, shining, black stripe confined to the facial projection and upper margin of mouth and a shining, black lateral portion of the face below the eyes; gena pruinose with a narrow, ventral, shining black stripe; frons shining black, anterior portion of frons mostly pruinose (except posterior margin of lunule) meeting pruinosity of face laterally, width of pruinosity along eye margin at level of antennae much wider than scape; posterior portion of frons bare and shining black; lunule dark brown; ocellar triangle with a few yellowish-white hairs visibly longer than the triangle; scape, pedicel and arista brown, third segment of antenna orange, 
<number box="[542,577,1817,1841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times as long as wide; arista about 
<number box="[1002,1037,1817,1841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="1.8">1.8</number>
times as long as third segment of antenna; occiput pruinose except for a narrow, shining black stripe along the postocular margin, dorsally; prementum brown; palpus absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,664,1888,1913]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum shining black except for pruinose spots close to postpronotum; mesonotum with uniform, short, yellowish-white, erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1111,1924,1949]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1436,1459]" captionTargetBox="[219,1402,252,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1412]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 1. Adult, lateral view; 2. Mesonotum, lateral view; 3. Head, lateral view; 4. Head, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255697/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[1095,1111,1925,1949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); postpronotum pruinose on anterior half; postalar callus shining black; scutellum shining black, heavily punctuated, with yellowish hairs; mesopleuron shining black except for proepisternum and anterior part of proepimeron; anepisternum, median part of katepisternum, anepimeron and katepimeron with yellow hairs. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[897,953,1856,1881]" pageId="3" pageNumber="279">Legs</emphasis>
. Fore coxa predominantly pruinose; dorsal half of hind coxa pruinose; mid coxa and ventral half of hind coxa shining black; trochanter shining black; femora shining black, thickened and entirely with yellow hairs, fore and mid femora with two rows of ventral spines on almost apical half, hind femur with two rows of distinct ventral spines reaching basal half as a field of bristles; tibiae shining black, basal third and apex orange and with yellowish hairs, mid tibia with a transverse row of ventroapical black bristles; tarsi orange except dark tarsomeres 
<number box="[906,950,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
, with dorsal and ventral yellowish hairs; pulvilli yellowish; claws dark brown, basal third orange. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,881,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline; veins mostly dark, yellowish in basal third, veins C and R 
<number box="[374,382,238,252]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="1.0">1</number>
yellowish in basal half of pterostigma; wing predominantly with microtrichiae, base of costal, 
<number box="[151,161,263,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="1.0">1</number>
st basal (br), 
<number box="[316,329,262,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="2.0">2</number>
nd basal (bm) and anal cells bare; calypter whitish; halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1087,1204,262,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1220,1325,262,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">
Figs 
<number box="[1279,1325,262,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Entirely with yellow hairs; tergite 
<number box="[445,459,299,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="1.0">1</number>
mostly black except lateral orange portion; tergite 
<number box="[1044,1058,299,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="2.0">2</number>
orange with median longitudinal black stripe reaching posterior margin; tergite 
<number box="[674,688,335,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="3.0">3</number>
predominantly black with a pair of anterolateral triangular orange spots ending short of the posterior margin; posterior margin of tergite 
<number box="[935,949,371,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="3.0">3</number>
orange; tergite 
<number box="[1125,1139,371,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="4.0">4</number>
black, densely punctuated and posteriorly orange (
<figureCitation box="[416,484,406,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[468,484,406,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); pregenital tergites black; sternite 
<number box="[876,890,407,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="1.0">1</number>
mostly black, posteriorly orange, entirely dusted and with long yellow hairs; sternite 
<number box="[576,590,443,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="2.0">2</number>
orange, dusted and with short yellow hairs; sternites 
<number box="[1220,1262,443,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
predominantly black, but anterior margin of sternite 
<number box="[582,596,479,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="3.0">3</number>
and posterior margin of sternite 
<number box="[976,990,479,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="4.0">4</number>
orange, both sternites dusted and with short hairs; hypandrium in lateral view with an pointed inner projection (
<figureCitation box="[994,1065,514,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[1049,1065,514,539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral margins of hypandrium nearly parallel in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[502,570,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[220,1402,210,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Myolepta pazukii Gilasian &amp; Reemer sp. nov. (male holotype). 5. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm; 6. Hypandrium, lateral view; 7. Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255698/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[554,570,551,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[592,719,550,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="280">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
